This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with forwarding data requests in Named Data Networking. It may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses forwarding table entries and name lookups. Additionally, it could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it explores semantic similarities between names. The paper also mentions the use of a semantic understanding function, which could place it in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses naming conventions and language, which could classify it under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
